Spa culture. Types of spa treatments and therapies in resorts: massage types, hydrotherapy, thermotherapy, kinesitherapy, other therapies (electrotherapy, salt therapy, light therapy etc.), mud therapy and relaxation therapies. Different spa packages in Estonian resorts. Nature-based therapies and wellbeing. Experience of nature-based wellness services. New service development concept. The course is combined with e-studies and study trips to organisations in the wellness and spa service sector.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide an overview of spa services and nature-based wellness services. The main topics are: definition of spa culture, types of spa treatments and nature-based wellness services, new service development concept. The course will give overview in spa packages design.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) knows and understands principles and methods of spa treatments, nature-based wellness therapies and new service development concept; 2) acquires knowledge and skills to spa treatments and nature-based wellness services; 3) acquires knowledge and skills to relevant academic literature set out in compulsory and recommended study materials and critically analyse and compare theories.
